   "source": [
    "# What is this?\n",
    "Simple glue-script to go from HiC-Pro to juicebox-pre.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Why?\n",
    "Because some people cannot sleep without making up some new file-standard, which can only be generated by their own software and used by -you guessed it- their own software.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data in vs out\n",
    "\n",
    "## HiC-pro: Validpairs\n",
    "Readname, chrA, PosA,StrA, chrB, PosB,StrB,MAPQ\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "HWI-D00645:88:C7HBDANXX:6:2216:4453:76782\tchr1\t13052\t+\tchr9\t130570482\t-\t574\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "## Juice*: Paired contacts\n",
    "```\n",
    "Readname, StrA, chrA, PosA, FragA, StrB, chrB, PosB, FragB, MAPQB, MAPQB\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "* str = strand (0 for forward, anything else for reverse) ##0 = fwd, 16 = rev\n",
    "* chr = chromosome (must be a chromosome in the genome)\n",
    "* pos = position\n",
    "* frag = restriction site fragment\n",
    "* mapq = mapping quality score\n",
    "\n",
    "If not using the restriction site file option, frag will be ignored. If not using mapping quality filter, mapq will be ignored."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2016-03-16T11:10:31.435078",
